## The Nature of Self and Reality

And as you act out what is important to you, what you prefer, as you radiate to each other this energy, this vibration, this frequency, you will each become more sensitized, more sensitive to each other. You'll be able to key off of each other more clearly without the negative confusion of certain habitual customs which now blind you from your hardest desire, certain social patterns which you will understand are simply creations of the mind, creations of fear, creations of doubt, of reservation, of distance.

You will understand that your core is indestructible. You are eternal, you are infinite, you are indestructible. You have been around forever, you're not going anywhere, you will always exist. That which was said in your film that you watched—that the name of creation is "I am"—is absolute in its truth. It is, it always has been, and it always will be. That which exists can only continue to exist; it will never become nonexistent. Because as nonexistence is its own realm, it already contains all the things that will never exist. Whatever doesn't fit in that realm is in the realm of existence, and whatever is in that realm has always existed, exists now, and always will, because there's nowhere else for it to go. Nonexistence is full up of all the things that will never exist. There is no room for existence there.

It is the polarity of creation—no beginning, no ending. It always is at every moment. And so, since you exist—I will assume I am not fantasizing—since you exist, you always have and you always will. You cannot be obliterated, you cannot be consigned to oblivion, you cannot be destroyed. You are indestructible, you are eternal, you are infinite. But you are ever changing. You are never the same, never from one second to the next.

Never allow yourselves to feel the change as the true constant in creation. The true stable foundation of existence is constant change, so that it does not stagnate, so that it is ever perpetuating. Creation is not over. It is not that everything has been created and God has sent everything off to run around and have fun. "Well, I created you, now go out and play." You are all—we are all together—God ever creating itself anew, ever changing, but always existing. Paradox yes, but when you deal with paradox, that's when you know you're close to the seed at the center, because only at the center do all apparent contradictions find themselves reconciled as one. Only from the center do all apparent polarities issue. They are all there, they are one thing. They only appear paradoxical, mutually exclusive, because of the vibrations in the realm in which you have chosen to perceive yourselves, because of the vibrations of realms that have the idea of polarity, of opposites.

You have created the ability—most creative, most creative of you—you have created the ability to take one thing and separate it into more than one thing, and even separate it into things that look like they have nothing to do with each other. Most creative, exceedingly creative—and I am not being facetious—it is the true measure of the power of creation that it can even, so to speak, fool itself into thinking it is not a part of that creation, into forgetting that it is what it is, that it is I AM. That is the power of creativity.

